Samba is a server Message block used for network file sharing protocol
SMB ran on top of Netbios using port 139
smb uses port 445
Samba is Linux implementation of SMB and allows windows systems to access linux shares and devices

we can perform a bruteforce attack on the samba server to get the creds
after that we can use a utility called SMBmap to enumerate the share drives list of contents
using smb_login in metasploit we can do otherwise using hydra we can do login
smbmap -H <domain/ip> -u <username> -p <password> to get the shares that are read/write only

to enter into shares use smbclient
smbclient -L \\\\<ip/domian>\\ -u <username> //to see the shares
smbclient \\\\<ip/domain>\\share$ -u <username> //to access the shares
smbclient \\\\<ip/domain>\\share -u <username> \\to access shares only

enum4linux is used to enumerate all the info
enum4linux -a <ip/domain>
enum4linux -a -u <username> -p <password> <domain/ip> //if smb doesnt have null login

